ce:section.ce:para:
UV–vis spectroscopic experiments were conducted for 6-MP to get the spectroscopic characteristics of the molecule and to investigate if the absorption peak could also be probed for analytical measurements from the solution (Fig. 3
                           ). The UV–vis spectra of 6-MP generated the absorption peak with the absorbance maxima of peak at 321 nm. The intensity of absorbance peak of 6-MP enhances linearly with the gradual increase in the concentration of 6-MP in the solution (cf. 
                           Fig. 3A). In order to propose a method of determination of 6-MP through the spectrophotometric method, the calibration plot was constructed and shown in Fig. 3B. The detection limit (3 s) and the quantification limit of 6-MP using this calibration has been obtained as 4.1 µM and 5.7 µM respectively.
